metatags.og:title: Answer to: Why is an athletes resting heart rate lower than an average persons?
metatags.og:description: Blood pressure is how the force of the blood that is being pumped out of your heart. An athlete has a lower heart rate because through exercise, they have a stronger heart; meaning that an athlete's heart can pump more blood and more oxygen out with one pump than a non-athlete's heart could.
